HDOCKlite v1.0 -- The ab initio docking engine of the HDOCK server (http://hdock.phys.hust.edu.cn/)
	     
This program performs the ab initio protein-protein and protein-RNA/DNA docking using
the intrinsic scoring functions for protein-protein and protein-RNA interactions based
on a hierarchical algorithm.

Here is an example to use HDOCKlite

	hdock 1CGI_r_b.pdb 1CGI_l_b.pdb -out Hdock.out
	creapl Hdock.out top100.pdb -nmax 100 -complex -models

where the first command does the ab initio docking and the second command creates the docked
complex models from the solutions in Hdock.out.

For more information about HDOCKlite, please type the programs or visit the help page of HDOCK server.


